text: Val d'Arry is a commune. It is found in the region Normandy in the Calvados department in the northwest of France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2017 and consists of the former communes of Noyers-Missy (the seat), Le Locheur and Tournay-sur-Odon.Arrêté préfectoral 8 September 2016 == References == Category:2017 establishments in France Category:Communes in Calvados
title: Val d'Arry
